criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Men and women aged 40-85 years old;

          -  BMI< 30 kg/m2;

          -  Patients suspected of having pancreatic cancer for whom an ultrasound endoscopic
             biopsy and/or biliary drainage is planned;

          -  Affiliation to, or beneficiary of, a social security scheme.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Woman who is pregnant or likely to become pregnant (without effective contraception)
             or breastfeeding ;

          -  Person in an emergency situation, person of full age subject to a legal protection
             measure, or unable to express consent;

          -  Biliary drainage or attempt at prior biliary drainage outside the center ;

          -  Preliminary oncological treatment for pancreatic pathology covered by the study;

          -  Clinical and/or image-visible (CT/MRI) carcinosis ;

          -  Ascites visible on imaging (CT/MRI) ;

          -  Impossibility to undergo the medical follow-up of the trial for geographical, social
             or psychological reasons;

          -  Contraindications to an endoscopic procedure.
